d response replaces the first — the customer never sees the rejected draft.","minimum_level":"Workflow","justification":"Evidence: Correctness is across sequenced LLM-involved stages (initial generation -> tone decision -> regeneration -> final delivery selection).\nLower-level miss-proof: Integration with forced flags/canned outputs can miss real sequencing leaks where draft timing/state from live model steps exposes the first response.\nFinal label: Workflow. Rejected Agentic because the behavior explicitly requires multi-step orchestration guarantee, not just one model judgment quality.","test_description":"Run end-to-end conversation with real LLM generation and real tone-check step configured to trigger regeneration; assert customer-visible channel only contains regenerated response while audit log retains rejected draft internally.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.01,"Integration":0.12,"System":0.02,"Agentic":0.3,"Workflow":0.55}}]}
